### Description

On some images, I got crash in SKCodec > GetScaledDimensions with AccessViolation exception.

![image](https://github.com/mono/SkiaSharp/assets/3595443/6f9fbc7b-b4ff-4ebd-b40c-6cbb42968b12)

The file content is stored in a memory stream, with using block so the buffer is not disposed.

Is it a know bug of Skia? Is there something I can do to catch the AccessViolation exception? or avoid the crash?

Thanks.

### Code

using (var memStream = new MemoryStream())
{
    using (var stream = await storageFile.OpenReadAsync())
    {
        await stream.CopyToAsync(memStream);
        memStream.Seek(0, SeekOrigin.Begin);
    }

    using (var skStream = new SKManagedStream(memStream))
    {
    using (var skData = SKData.Create(skStream))
    {
    using (var codec = SKCodec.Create(skData))
    {
